FBIS3-56323 "drsov010_a_94069" FBIS-SOV-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Shumeyko: `No Question' of Handing Over Kurils LD1301152894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1413 GMT 13 Jan 94 LD1301152894 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The speaker of the Russian Federation Council Vladimir Shumeyko has said that he backs Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin in terms of the disputed Northern Territories. He believes that the islands of Kunashir, Iturup, Shikotan and Habomai, claimed by Japan, "belong to Russia and there is no question of handing them over now." Shumeyko was giving his first news conference as Speaker of the Upper House of the Russian Federal Assembly. Shumeyko said that the prime minister's view was shared by the other Cabinet members. At the same time Shumeyko admitted that this view was different somewhat from the official one.
